Rare & Gorgeous 1967 Ford Mustang GTA Hardtop

The next amazing vehicle up for grabs in our Benicia showroom is this gorgeous 1967 Ford Mustang GTA 2 Door Hardtop Coupe with Lime Gold Metallic exterior paint and a matching Ivy Gold interior.  This amazing survivor comes equipped with the factory 289 cid V-8 engine under the hood along with the numbers-matching C-4 automatic transmission, both of which have been fully restored back to like-new condition.  This classic also has a Magnaflow dual exhaust, an Edelbrock 600 cfm carburetor and intake, 3.00 rear gears, and fantastic documentation to show its originality.  You must see this one in person to truly appreciate it.
100% Restored w/ Ample Documentation & Marti Report

The current owner of this 1967 Ford Mustang GTA Hardtop purchased it back in 2008 and painstakingly restored it himself back to full factory specifications.  He informs us that he is the third lifetime owner and this beauty is in the original factory color, plus he ensured that everything on this gorgeous muscle car was 100% correct for the make/model.  It took him extensive time to track down misc. parts but the effort was well worth it- this vehicle looks as good as new and drives like a champion.

Additionally, we have a full Marti Report to show this classic’s authenticity plus ample documentation like the original window sticker, build receipts, MCA judging certificates and more.  The complete restoration was completed in 2009 and this one has been driven approximately 12,000 miles since that time, so there are only the slightest signs of wear to be found anywhere.  This 1967 Ford Mustang GTA is literally picture perfect.
One of the Nicest Examples You’ll Find Anywhere

Overall, this 1967 Ford Mustang GTA Hardtop is one of the most original, pristine examples that we have ever seen outside of a museum.  Given that these models are scarce to begin with, finding one of this caliber is next to impossible and there’s no way it remains available for long.  The asking price is likely too conservative for such an amazing muscle car.  For more information about this vehicle, visit our Benicia, California showroom, give us a call at

description: Stk. 2223  1967 Ford Mustang    This 1967 Mustang convertible is a nicely restored example of a very popular automobile. It has had only two owners in 50 years, the current owner possessing it for the last 18. The exterior was beautifully refinished (2000) in Dark Green that is very similar to Ford's Dark Moss Green. Stylish Mustang steel wheels, narrow whitewall tires and a classic chrome luggage rack provide nice finishing touches to the exterior. The Saddle Tan vinyl interior was restored back to original in 2000. Seats, door cards and carpeting are all well presented. A custom wood grained steering wheel replaces the original 'padded' wheel and the radio is an aftermarket AM/FM/cassette. The tan power top is in very good condition and has a tight vinyl boot. Our Mustang is powered by a 289ci small block that has been totally rebuilt. This car was a C code (289/2V) car from the factory, but we are not  sure that this is the original engine. However, knowing what we do about the history of the car, it is doubtful that the engine was ever changed. Interestingly, the transmission is a 3-speed manual with floor shift. This was the standard transmission for the '67 Mustang, but most folks who ordered a V8 usually ordered the automatic or the 4-speed manual. Brakes are standard 4-wheel drum units. This is a very nice Mustang convertible that should sell quickly. Please call 800-650-1055 or visit our website at www.autobarnclassiccars.com for additional information. ALL VEHICLES SOLD AS IS

description: This is the classic pony car with a very different attitude.  The 1986 Ford Mustang SVO took an American muscle icon and added a dose of energy pumping turbo power for a rare package that will make you realize this is a rare value-priced sleeper.

We all wanted more power in the '80s but we weren't sure if some regulations were going to outlaw our favorite cars.  Ford decided one way to approach these unsure times was with a traditional V8, and cool limited edition turbo car that was lighter but made the same power.  The guys at Ford's Special Vehicle Operations (SVO) developed this limited edition coupe that carried the Mustang's fastback style, but with some very distinctive touches.  It's instantly recognizable as a special car with features like a unique front end, offset hood scoop for the turbo's ram air, and dual rear spoilers.  All of these unique elements are present today on this fastback, and they look great against the factory-correct 2A Bright Red paint.  When these special SVO cars were new, they were about double the price of the base Mustang LX, and so you can understand that this is a rare model with only 3,382 produced in 1986.

Just like the exterior, the interior shares many premium Mustang GT elements, but has enough unique pieces for the SVO to be all its own.  It starts with the exclusive sport bucket seats with added adjustable supports, a cool SVO three-spoke steering wheel, and a Hurst short throw shifter.  Because this came at a premium price, it also came loaded with features.  This includes power windows, power locks, electric rear defrost, digital clock, and provisions for air conditioning.  There's even a newer AM/FM/CD stereo with auxiliary input to play all of your modern tunes.  It's a true driver's car.  That's why you get the full gauge pack, including large tach to make sure you can see when this turbo motor really catches its breath.

The advantage of getting a car from the SVO team meant it was built by engineers who wanted to make the best performance machine around.  That's why this special Mustang is much more than just bolting on a turbo.  We believe the 2.3-liter turbocharged, and intercooled, four-cylinder engine is original, and we know it's both smart and tough. This is a computer-controlled unit that was given beefed-up internals to handle even more boost than the engineers were dialing in.  Ford liked to tout that this turbo motor was just like a V8, and there were not far off considering this Mustang made as much horsepower as it stablemate 5.0 GT.  But what made the difference of the SVO was that it had a true European flair on the road.  That comes from features like the four-wheel disc brakes, Koni shocks, McPherson strut front suspension, and quad shock rear end.  Plus there were other great driving features such as the Borg Warner five-speed manual transmission, versatile 3.73 rear gears, and power assisted rack & pinion steering,

Complete with original title documentation, this 2nd-owner (who just rescued it out of the original owners garage) SVO remains a lot of fun, and the price for this low batch collectible can't be beat.  Call today!!

description: For sale in our Chicago showroom is a slick black 1965 Ford Mustang.  Historically the Ford Mustang was a real game changer in the automotive world and really took the American public by storm when it was unveiled at the New York World's Fair on April 17, 1964 and eventually became a motoring icon. Engine choices were originally a 260 Cubic Inch V8 and 170 Cubic Inch Inline 6 Cylinder but were later upgraded to the 289 and 200 which increased horsepower and got this little "Pony" car up to speed without hesitation.  The 289 that originally came in this little beauty has been replaced with a very peppy 351 Windsor V8 that gives a nice roar as you dice through traffic or cruise on the open highway. The shiny black exterior features American Racing wheels and is matched nicely to the black interior with bucket seats and original dash and gauges with the addition of a digital stereo by Custom Autosound and Sunpro gauges.  The classic black plastic steering wheel has been kept in place and a wood steering wheel is also included.  The windows have just the right amount of tint to keep those harmful rays out and help to give this car a sinister look on the road.  Located in our Chicago showroom, this classic 1965 Ford Mustang can be seen including an HD video and pictures at www.gatewayclassiccars.com.  For additional information please call (708) 444-4488 or email chicago@gatewayclassiccars.com.
